file=Product/ux/operational/commands/ux-commands.md · tb=\| Trigger phrases \| Skill \| Shortcut \| · tb=\|---\|---\|---\| · tb=\| "do we know", "have we researched", "find the study", "is this known", "cite research" \| research-repository \| /repo \| · tb=\| "run a study", "interview users", "usability test", "survey", "design the research" \| study-design \| /study \| · tb=\| "what does the data say", "synthesize", "findings", "how confident", "the takeaway" \| synthesis-discipline \| /synth \| · tb=\| "what are customers saying", "support themes", "reviews", "NPS verbatims" \| voice-of-customer-intake \| /voc \| · p:Precedence=1. Any new-study request routes to research-repository FIRST (query before you run); /study on an un-queried question bounces to /repo.\n2. A claim entering a PRD must pass synthesis-discipline's confidence flag — unflagged claims bounce.\n3. Voice-of-customer patterns are directional evidence, not verdicts — strong ones become /study GAPs, never product decisions.\n